The paper discusses the use of linear approximations to explain complex models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions contextual explanation networks (CENs), which are a type of neural network used for generating explanations (cs.CL). The analysis of the properties of explanations produced by different methods may also be relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV) research.
